12f3823c-3047-484b-aa37-75d64a3f8b5e.do_description: To make the output, you have to...take the 3x3 area with a yellow square and move it into a 3x3 area corresponding to where the yellow square is within the 9 squares. Then make all other squares within the other 9 squares black and any grey squares within the 9 squares black. The lines of grey stay.
12f3823c-3047-484b-aa37-75d64a3f8b5e.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid size
12f3823c-3047-484b-aa37-75d64a3f8b5e.see_description: In the input, you should see...9 squares created by lines of grey

25c77358-cf42-4b04-b0cf-7f4840e4e49a.do_description: To make the output, you have to...change all colored patterns and return them to black squares except the middle left square which should be the same as what the bottom left square looks like on the input square
25c77358-cf42-4b04-b0cf-7f4840e4e49a.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid
25c77358-cf42-4b04-b0cf-7f4840e4e49a.see_description: In the input, you should see...9 black squares of grey lines and  patterns in every square

48038a2f-920b-47df-8b73-202254a28fe4.do_description: To make the output, you have to...change the colors to three or four random patterns
48038a2f-920b-47df-8b73-202254a28fe4.grid_description: The output grid size...will be one of the smaller sections
48038a2f-920b-47df-8b73-202254a28fe4.see_description: In the input, you should see...grids with a single grey barrier

666ad117-ef9c-4d1f-9339-a5b8c66ecc5b.do_description: To make the output, you have to...find the only 3x3 grid in the input that contains a yellow square. Make each of the 9 3x3 grids all black, then copy and paste the grid with the yellow square into the 3x3 grid that corresponds to the 3x3 grid square that the yellow square is in. So if the yellow square is in the middle square in the grid, copy that entire grid into the middle 3x3 grid. Finally, change any grey squares inside the grid to black.
666ad117-ef9c-4d1f-9339-a5b8c66ecc5b.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input grid size
666ad117-ef9c-4d1f-9339-a5b8c66ecc5b.see_description: In the input, you should see...9 squares, each measuring 3x3 which are created by grey lines that form a hashtag

7981adeb-b903-4c6e-b08c-4420b6f1f701.do_description: To make the output, you have to...make all sections black and leave one section color.

7981adeb-b903-4c6e-b08c-4420b6f1f701.see_description: In the input, you should see...grid with many sections

b8c4aef8-bc67-44bc-99d8-6485c4892062.see_description: In the input, you should see...grids with a single grey edge

e2d2cf43-2e4e-4fd9-a249-2cf9e726b5ad.do_description: To make the output, you have to... make all the 3x3 squares fully black, then recreate the pattern from the bottom left square of the input into the top right square of the output grid.
